# Line-ending policy: store every text file as LF in the repo AND check it
# out as LF in the working tree, on every platform.
#
# Why: this is a cross-platform repo with LF-enforcing tooling.
#   - Prettier (`format:check`) defaults to endOfLine: lf and fails on CRLF.
#   - s6 run scripts + shell scripts MUST be LF — a CRLF in a
#     `#!/usr/bin/with-contenv bash` shebang breaks the service.
#   - Python / ruff are LF by convention.
# Without this, a Windows checkout with core.autocrlf=true silently swaps
# LF↔CRLF, which (a) made local `format:check` disagree with CI and (b)
# risks committing CRLF blobs that fail the format gate. `eol=lf` forces
# LF in the working tree too, so editors + tooling see the same bytes CI does.
* text=auto eol=lf

# Shell + s6 service scripts: LF is load-bearing (shebang/exec), make it
# explicit so no future attribute change can relax it.
*.sh text eol=lf
*.bash text eol=lf
**/rootfs/etc/services.d/*/run text eol=lf
**/rootfs/etc/cont-init.d/* text eol=lf

# Binary assets — never normalize / diff as text.
*.png binary
*.jpg binary
*.jpeg binary
*.gif binary
*.ico binary
*.webp binary
*.woff binary
*.woff2 binary
*.pdf binary
*.onnx binary
*.engine binary
*.pt binary
*.pth binary
